# Cloudflare Pages / Netlify _headers file — OpenMW WASM pthread build
#
# Copy this file into the root of your published directory (the same folder
# as openmw.html) for hosts that support the Netlify _headers format:
#   - Cloudflare Pages
#   - Netlify (alternative to netlify.toml)
#
# For the NON-PTHREAD (single-threaded) build you do NOT need this file at all.
# The non-pthread build works without cross-origin isolation headers and can be
# hosted on GitHub Pages, any S3 bucket, or any other static file host.

/*
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN

/openmw.html
  Cache-Control: no-cache, no-store, must-revalidate
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp

/*.wasm
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp

/*.data
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
  Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin
  Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy: require-corp
